      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "I think without the custom code we cannot reason very insightfully much about the prescribed \"relevance\" metric or the measurements it led to. I'd be surprised if one could say that \"Bitcoin Core nodes are less relevant when I score them against matching my local mempool policy\" and apply that logic to the whole network.\n\n> I'm curious what your mempool policy is.\n\nIndeed, without this and the source we can't do anything but speculate. Is this the branch? https://github.com/rebroad/bitcoin/blob/moorlane-core-master.wip\n\n> But I also think you should close this issue until you can reproduce it with bitcoin core.\n\nYes, I'm not sure what we can action or even discuss here particularly.",
