      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "> it's custom code that I've been using since 2022 - it rates a node based on how much of the data received ends up in the mempool and evicts the node with the lowest score.\n\nSo you created a custom policy that sounds like it favors peers running relay policies like those implemented in Knots and now you claim that somehow this translates into \"Core being less relevant than Knots.\"\n\nYour statement is, at most, applicable to your own node, and has no relevance to Bitcoin Core users.",
